&lt;p&gt;Theatre Support Worker&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imperial College Healthcare NHS trust is one of the largest acute Trusts in the country and in partnership with Imperial College London; it is one of the UK’s first academic health science centres (AHSCs). The creation of the AHSC is a major advance for patient care, clinical teaching and scientific invention and innovation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Theatre Support Worker who shares our ambition and vision to deliver the best of care by the best people and has the drive to take us forward, by ensuring the Trust continues to be the first choice for patients and our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be reliable, flexible, organised, friendly and confident with experience of working within a very busy and fast-pace patient facing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working days and or shift patterns will be agreed by the line manager to meet the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All successful applicants must undertake and pass to a suitable standard the Trust&#39;s math and English test.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are enthusiastic about education. We promise that we will guide your development; this will be tailored to meet your needs and also the needs of the service. You will have the opportunity to develop or enhance your skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All of our hospitals are near quick transport access to Westfield shopping and leisure centre, the West End, and a range of local bars, cafes and restaurants - ideal for team socials!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
